BOB MARCO , tucked up towards the rail tracking the embattled leaders, awaited room nearing the lane, worked between rivals leaving mid stretch, altered out late and closed willingly. RICOCHET took over between rivals early then secured the rail and set a pressured pace, dueled inside runners from the three eighths, failed to go on nearing the sixteenth pole and weakened late. ONE TWO KID settled off the rail early on, moved up and bid three deep into the far turn, sparred between rivals from upper stretch to about mid stretch then gave way. MINT GAME , well placed and settled towards the rail, eased out into the stretch but failed to kick on. FERMAT , sluggish from the gate, lagged back, came under a ride three wide leaving the far turn but failed to respond. ARISTOCAT , two wide outside RICOCHET contesting the early pace, fought on between rivals past the five sixteenths then surrendered through the drive.
